New Super Eagles invitee Akinkunmi Amoo signed off for the international break in style as he scored his first goal for FC Copenhagen inspiring them to a 1-0 win over FC Nordsjælland . The 19-year-old was handed his first league start since his move from Sweden as he started on the left hand of the attack with fellow Nigerian Paul Mukairu starting on the other flank. The former Golden Eaglets attacking midfielder hit the ground running from the blast of the whistle, needing to show himself to the fans present as he tapped home from four yards the only goal of the match following an assist from Khouma Babacar.   Boris Becker faces trial in London     Belgrade 2022: : Sports Minister lauds Brume’s silver…     Lobi Stars reappoint Iorfa as Vice Chairman   Speaking to the club’s media after the game, the match-winner praised the fans for their part in the victory stating that the goal meant a lot to him and his family.  “I’m so happy to score my first goal today! It means a lot to me and my family. It was great to be the match-winner and secure the victory, even though we should have scored more goals in the match. It took hard work to get the three points, but that’s how it should be, “ Amoo said. He stated further: “It’s great to be able to help the team and at the same time make sure the fans go home happy. It was an important victory and we have to fully focus on the championship.” The pacy attacker had a fantastic game rating of 8.7, the highest rating in the game, making four key passes, the most in the encounter, creating one chance and also putting in a defensive shift with two interceptions and one tackle.